Hawk the Hunter
()xxxxxx{>==============================>

by Jonathan B. Himes

You awake outside the fortified Keep of your family, aware only that the Mindsword has been wrenched from you by a powerful Warlock. . .

This is a Story of Heroic Deeds with one true goal but infinite paths to find it.  It's an unofficial sequel to the 1980 film Hawk the Slayer, but will make sense as a stand-alone as you uncover what happened to you.

The realm of Hawk the Hunter is fraught with dangerous trails that twist and turn, so mapping with notes is essential. Save your game frequently in case of mishaps! Leave no stone unturned.
Type HELP for more startup tips, further hints (a walk-through of sorts), and credits.  Don't use SCRIPT ON, which interferes with Quest code.
Last you remember, your giant comrade Gort was with you in the South, spying on a secret conclave of Black Wizards.  But you were waylaid by a Warlock. . .

Courtyard
Cobblestones line the quadrangle of this entrance to RavenWood Keep, the small castle of your family now adorned solely by a torn flag in the lookout tower.  An old stable lies in a corner.  The rest of this area is swallowed by the surrounding gloom of the forest.  The iron-bound doors of the castle, damaged and slightly ajar, are set in the stone walls to the north.
You can go southeast, north or in.

You are disoriented and cannot recall how you got here. You will regain your faculties by degrees as you recover your wits (type HELP STATS at any time to learn more). . .
