Main Hall
In this spacious hall, dark wooden benches and receiving tables have been overturned.  Stale odors waft in from serving doors to the north, and doused torches hang from sconces in the corners, one of them lit by gutted flame.  Also on prominent display, an elaborate tapestry graces the north wall.  An ancient battle axe hangs proudly over the iron doors at the entrance.  A stout door to the east has been barred shut.
You can go west, south, east or north.

