Kitchen
Windows in the north wall admit cool air, and a fair amount of light.  A blackened oven takes up one wall, and long wooden tables serve for food preparation.  The pantry takes up another wall with shelves in the stone.  Any edibles look to have been scavenged some time ago.
You can go south.

> x pantry

> x pantry
On the cobwebbed wall of the pantry shelves, you find sundry cooking implements, mostly broken.
They contain a tinderbox.
