CrossRoads
This ancient intersection near Castle RavenWood, trails barely discernible to each other through the fog and foliage, is overgrown in these dark days with a canopy of thick limbs and vines.
 You can go south, northeast or west.

You hear the loud screech of a goshawk.
It intercepts a pigeon or a dove far above the canopy overhead. For a second between an opening in the leaves you see them clash. A frayed roll of tiny parchment bounces down from the branches below the wheeling birds.  By the time it lands, it has come untied.
Hawk the Hunter needs rest in a soothing spa, or maybe a cauldron.
