> west

Old Mule Track
An old market path, wide enough for mule-drawn carts, is on the verge of being reclaimed by the wilderness. As dark shadows and mist roll in from either side, you can hear faint bellows and cries, as of wanderers off the track, now the prey of lurking vermin.
You can go east, south or northwest.

