Woodsmans Clearing
A few trails spill into this grassy field where the canopy of leaves thins out enough to show the grey sky.  Many stumps attest to active clearing by loggers in days gone by, but there are still a few large boled trees that dot the perimeter. One of them has a rusty axe embedded in the trunk at eye level. A glint round back of it also catches your eye.
You can go east, south or north.

