Forest of Weir
Stepping to the fringe of the murky woodlands, bounded by a high eldritch gate, you hear eerie sounds of woe and gibbering madness.  A cluster of skeletal corpses near the Forest Gate catches your eye. When you turn to look closer, it is all gone. You misdoubt yourself.
You can go south or north.

