A guard room
This small room has stone stairs in the corner going up and down, arrow loops in one wall, and several small holes in the other through which you can see dim lights and hear loud voices.  It sounds as though a large assembly has been mustered by Voltan in the room beyond.
You can go up, down or east.

You notice a small notepaper on the floor, but before you can pick it up, you are startled at the sight of an armed guard pointing a pike in your face. He pulls out an olifaunt and whets his lips to blow...
> attack guard

> attack guard
You swing your Mindsword and hit, doing 11 points of damage (14 hits left).
Guard swings at you and hits, doing 2 points of damage.

The guard drops from fright as much as fight, and as the dust settles, you overhear Voltan ranting in the adjoining chamber, which you observe through a hole in the wall:

"Speak up, sorcerer!  Or shall I say, 'scientist'?  Your efforts thus far have yielded minions who walk and talk, but are too slow and weak.  Or they prefer their old haunts and habits."  The old man in the lab coat sighs and lectures Voltan in mild tones you cannot make out.

"Very well," Voltan hisses. "With the kettle to serve as our own cauldron, we shall quicken those 're-animations', as you say.  But they had best be done before the Dark Sword is fetched here, that we may open the new portals, else you shall return to Kleel the old way."  The scientist shivers as Voltan snickers, "Yes ... yes!  A little taste of the undead is less than appetizing, it seems.  Heheheheheheh."

Your view begins to blur, and the notepaper you saw on the floor whips into the air like a leaf in the wind, in fact joining other leaves in the gloomy forest paths.
Your score went up by 10!

