Great Hall
Here in the imposing hall of the Fortress, the High Abbot would receive dignitaries of various holy orders.  Now all is a shambles, the carved chairs kicked in and the gilt trim smeared with grime, or worse.  In the dim light, you can make out the still-pristine chapel door open to the east, narrow double doors to the north, and steps to the west leading up to a heavily armored door, above which you descry lookout slits from a guard room.  An upside-down crucifix hangs on the west wall.
As you gaze toward the chapel, you notice a well-armed minion, seemingly roused from unhallowed liturgy, rushing at you in a frenzy.
You can go south, west or north.
You can see a minion, a crucifix and a font.

From the double doors to the north, you hear plaintive feminine cries for help.
Minion has seen you, and is going to attack!
Minion swings at you and misses.
One by one, Minions emerge to drag the dead back to the chapel.

Your view begins to blur as it reassumes the features of bewildering forest paths.

