Chapel
Once an ornate sanctuary, this chapel now looks like a garbage-strewn cemetary.  All articles of devotion have been upturned and smashed to bits, the stone tiles smeared with dung, and a small dias in the center now holds a humongous kettle that bubbles over with rancid red foam like a Cauldron.
You can go west.
You can see a crypt, conclave of wizards, a squad of minions and Black Wizard.

From crimson depths within the Cauldron, the familiar cowl of the Black Wizard rises before your eyes, somehow still dry, and fully alive!  Lifting a red talon, he commands arterial spray from the Cauldron to assault you!
You gasp as the crimson spray deflects to the floor, your genuflections having formed a holy barrier. The Wizard curses at you for this thwarting of his unhallowed powers.
Squad of minions has seen you, and is going to attack!
Black Wizard has seen you, and is going to attack!
Squad of minions swings at you and misses.
Black Wizard swipes with his rending claw  and misses.
Raising his paw, the wizard intones a mesmerizing litany, then lifts two fingers.  The Chapel door screeches shut and bolts itself. The Black Wizard pauses his canticle to tell you: "The Dark One is being fed and dressed for his final consummation, but will be with us presently!"
