The Casket lid flies open, and the dark figure of Voltan springs forth onto the small dias next to the wizard.  His pallid eye, now a pink dot in a face like rotten meat, blazes beside the metal gauze in his helmet. With the rosary beads of the Abbot on his scrawny neck, he looms over the Cauldron, black cape billowing out behind him as the smell of blood fills the chapel.
Voltan grins menacingly as the wizard bestows the Dark Sword in his tight-gloved hands. "Gog and Magog!  A Black Blade to rival the weapon of my whining ancestors."  He turns to you.  "Look well at this boon, little brother.  The articles of your superstitious creed were right about Life after Death!  Behold, I have undergone baptisms unimaginable, yet here I am in the flesh to escort you to the Gates of Hell!"
