"Whore of Babylon, come forth!" Out of the shadows behind the dais, a forlorn figure in a bridal veil totters forward at his beckoning.

Voltan's surly grin goes slack as he continues:  "Ten thousand times have I dreamed of killing you slowly, painfully... and now... with equal abandon shall I enjoy the marriage bed, wedding Elian as I was meant to."  The wizard, turning his hood in surprise, interrupts to ask if he just said "bed-wetting."
